**who —** The Prophet — Lolla-Wossiky become Tenskwa-Tawa, Ta-Kumsaw's brother — a one-eyed former drunk turned visionary who chooses pacifism and founds Prophetstown, ending in the Tippy-Canoe massacre

**what —** Lolla-Wossiky become Tenskwa-Tawa, Ta-Kumsaw's brother — a one-eyed former drunk turned visionary who chooses pacifism and founds Prophetstown, ending in the Tippy-Canoe massacre

**where —** ALV · The Tales of Alvin Maker — Orson Scott Card (1987–2003; finale 2026)  Framework inputs: Alvin Maker; the Unmaker; the knacks; the Crystal City; the greensong  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** He is the cost of refusing the sword: a prophet whose people die unresisting, and whose answer to the slaughter marks every guilty hand — the book's deepest wound.

**how —** Crystallized from Orson Scott Card's The Tales of Alvin Maker.

**◌ the mythos —** He is the cost of refusing the sword: a prophet whose people die unresisting, and whose answer to the slaughter marks every guilty hand — the book's deepest wound. a being of the folk-magic frontier and the war of Making and Unmaking

